div1.p:
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the County of King. HABEAS CORPUS The People of the United States of America, to J. C. Mitchell Chief of Police: We command you, that you have the body of George W. Anderson by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said George W. Anderson shall be called or charged, before the HON. C. H. Hanford, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the Court House in the City of Seattle Washington Territory at 5 o'clock P.M. of this day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the said George W. Anderson And have you then and there this writ.
Witness the HON C. H. Hanford Richard A. Jones, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 2nd day of October A.D. 1889. R. M. Hopkins Clerk. By H. T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.

E T No. 7264 In the District Court, Third Judicial District, Holding Terms at Seattle, W.T.
In the Matter of the Application of Geroge W. ANderson For Writ of Habeas Corpus. HABEAS CORPUS.
Returned and filed this 3rd day of October A.D. 1889 R. M. Hopkins Clerk. By H. T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.
